  @contract  skips non-note plans/cols; optional `deleted` event-set excluded from the walk  @ 336
  @invariant  deleted corpses still live in col.events snapshot until next rebuild  @ 337
  @invariant  a freshly placed note is unbounded: endppq = util.OPEN, no authored ceiling  @ 788
  @invariant  universal tail pass derives the real tail (next onset/take length) each rebuild  @ 789
  @contract  caller pre-pins (ppq, ppqL, rpb) onto `update` before calling  @ 790
  @contract  col nil only for a chord sprout (no column yet): no prev-vel to inherit, lane pre-set  @ 791
  @invariant  notes ordered by entry; members re-resolved via cells[row], never held event refs  @ 1116
  @contract  arms on a note col's first pitch stop; pins (row, chan) until shift release  @ 1136
  @contract  returns true iff consumed; false lets the drain fall through (to value-digit entry)  @ 1137
  @contract  re-striking a gesture pitch toggles it off; freed slots are reused lowest-first  @ 1138
  @contract  spreadChan strikes walk channels up from home; plain strikes stack home-channel lanes  @ 1139
  @invariant  pins (col,row,part); overwrites a place keep-below, steps the sub-caret right  @ 1257
  @invariant  field re-read via cells[row] each keystroke; undo snapshots drive backspace-restore  @ 1258
  @contract  selection must be exactly one grid column; multi-col selection is a no-op  @ 2737
  @invariant  a 1-col block stays contiguous when it lands on the destination col  @ 2738
  @contract  cursor follows to the destination column (single event and selection alike)  @ 2739
  @contract  refuse if dest col has any onset in source's row extent (note: note-on; else any event)  @ 2740
  @invariant  source's row extent = selection's [r1,r2] for a block, moved event's onset row for a single  @ 2741
  @invariant  tails (either direction) clipped by tm's tail pass; never block  @ 2742
  @contract  reentrancy-guarded; bails on no-take (page shows placeholder)  @ 3678
  @contract  takeChanged=true resets ec and re-reads resolution/length/timeSigs  @ 3679
  @contract  grid + ctx rebuild each call; pushMute at end  @ 3680
  @contract  a column's cells/ghosts carry while its events table + projection epoch are unchanged  @ 3681
  @contract  tv consumes configChanged only for transient-frame release and mute pulse  @ 3994
  @contract  rebuild is driven by tm's 'rebuild' signal — closes the (cm, tm) double-fire race  @ 3995
  @contract  non-transient FRAME_KEYS write while transient override active routes into releaseTransientFrame  @ 3996
